END--><br>
<br>
I. Overview<br>
II. Savagery<br>
III. Hand-To-Hand<br>
IV. Miscellaneous<br>
V. Suggestions<br>
VI. Conclusion<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I. Overview</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
We've seen a couple small changes in 1.56 which have done a good deal to improve our melee ability.  It's quite noticable how much of an improvement having the Attack Speed Debuff style work actually is.  I now swing 2-3 times for every single attack of my enemy in PvE.  There are some minor issues that I would like to bring up with the Hand-To-Hand style lines; couple small additions of to-hit bonuses on a couple styles and an addition of low damage to one of them as well.  The Savagery line is looking pretty good, save for the perpetual bug of randomly resisting our own buffs.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>II. Savagery</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
In many views, this should be the 'bread-n-butter' line for the Savage. Without this line, the Savage becomes a dual-wield/parry class, or a Berserker II. There is still concern that the cost-benefit ratio still has not reached an acceptable level. The recent increase in duration and decrease in costs has helped some, but some of the abilities are still not showing much combat performance improvement when compared to performance when not using them at all.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Bugs</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Savage Abilities Not Giving Valuable Info</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The Savagery buffs are giving most of the information about the abilities, but they are not giving the most important information:  what they actually do.  The delve information lists duration, cost, etc, but it does not list an effect.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Resisting Own Buffs</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The Savage still can sometimes resist their own buffs.  This needs to be addressed, as it has been an issue since the inception of the class.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Issues</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>DPS Buff Increase Not Enough, Especially at Lower Levels</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
For instance, the DPS buff. At level 1, the buff increases DPS by 5%. On a level 20, 7.1 dps weapon, this is little more than a .3dps increase. This is barely noticable. Even with the high level version, the 25% DPS increase on a 16.5dps weapon only increases the DPS of the weapon to 20.6. Through the damage formulae, this works out to be roughly equivalent to an 8dps Damage Add. However, the damage provided by the DPS buff is all subject to the melee resistance of the target, which Damage Adds are not. The buff needs to exceed that of other self damage add buffs in the game because of it's much shorter duration and much higher cost.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Suggestion: Alter the range of the buffs 10%, 15%, 20%, 25%, 30%, 35%.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>III. Hand-to-Hand</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The main concern with the style line is that there are no 'anytime' styles that grant to-hit bonuses or have any real damage associated with them.  The line needs at least one style with one or the other, really.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Issues</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Anytime Styles Lacking Damage Production</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
There are two useful anytime styles in the HTH line:  Kelgor's Might (PBAE Atk Spd Debuff) and Taunting Call (High Defensive Bonus).  Wild Call is too low level a style to produce quality damage at a later level, and is very bad for the Savage to use with its Medium Penalty to defense.  Kelgor's Claw isn't useful because the Evade enhancement isn't noticable, and is overshadowed by Taunting Call's high defensive bonus.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Suggestion:<br>
<br>
1. Add a &quot;Low&quot; attack bonus to Taunting Call.<br>
2. Add a &quot;Low&quot; attack bonus and &quot;Low&quot; damage bonus to Kelgor's Claw.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Clan's Might - No To-Hit Bonus</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Clan's Might is the followup to Clan's Call; it does the exact same damage as Clan's call, but can hit 2 targets.  However, it actually ends up doing much less damage than Clan's Call because it does not have an attack bonus associated with it.  This style is a second teir style off a positional opener.  It deserves more power than it currently has.  Right now, it's more useful to simply re-use Clan's Call for the same damage and better chance to hit.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Suggestion:  Add a &quot;Medium&quot; attack bonus to Clan's Might.  </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Clan's Might - Bleed Style Removed</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
When the Hand-To-Hand line was introduced, Clan's Might had a Bleed effect associated with it.  This effect is no longer listed on the Herald, and has never worked.  Where did it go?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Suggestion:  Return the Bleed effect to Clan's Might.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>+Evade/+Parry Styles</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
We are not noticing that using these styles actually has any effect on our chance to evade/parry.  If the effect is there and functioning, it is not intense enough to be noticable to the eye.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Suggestion:  Enhance the +Evade/+Parry styles to increase the chance more.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>IV. Miscellaneous Issues / Bugs</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
1. The Savage retains the small shield ability. However, upon becoming a Savage, the player can no longer equip small shields.  This either needs to be fixed, or the ability needs to be removed from the Savage.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>V. Suggestions</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Sense Aggression</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - this would be an ability added to the Savagery line. Radius: 350, Duration: 10s, Cost: 25% health/instant, Casting Time: Instant, Effect: Cause Savage to see 'shadowed' form of all stealthers within the radius of effect for the duration of the ability. Midgard needs a class with anti-stealth abilities to counter Albion's and Hibernia's. This ability would help distance the Savage from the Berserker's role in Midgard as well. With the health cost so high, and instant, this spell could not be used to solo hunt assassins, but it would be useful in helping protect a group of friends. Place this at Spec 40 in Savagery.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Kelgor's Recovery</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - the biggest problem with soloing a Savage in PvE is the downtime.  Yellow-con mobs will often take the Savage down to 1/4 health, leaving a long rest before fighting again.  Kelgor's Recovery would fix this; it would be a non-combat only ability that would slowly draw points from Endurance and increase the rate of HP regeneration as follows:<br>
<br>
Spec 10: Kelgor's Refreshment - each non-combat tick reduces End 1% and replaces 2% HP.<br>
Spec 20: Kelgor's Aid - each non-combat tick reduces End 4% and replaces 7% HP.<br>
Spec 30: Kelgor's Revitalization - each non-combat tick reduces End 8% and replaces 13% HP.<br>
Spec 40: Kelgor's Recovery - each non-combat tick reduces End 12% and replaces 20% HP.<br>
<br>
(Do not replace Kelgor's Boon with this ability, though.  Kelgor's Boon shoulds stay.)<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>VI. Conclusion</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Bugs</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
1.  Savages are still resisting their own self-buffs.<br>
2.  Savages retain the Small Shields ability, but cannot equip the shields.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Suggestions</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
1.  Alter the DPS buff to increase on the following table: 10%, 15%, 20%, 25%, 30%, 35%.<br>
2.  Add a &quot;Low&quot; attack bonus to Taunting Call.<br>
3.  Add a &quot;Low&quot; attack bonus and &quot;Low&quot; damage bonus to Kelgor's Claw.<br>
4.  Add a &quot;Medium&quot; attack bonus to Clan's Might. <br>
5.  Return the Bleed effect to Clan's Might.<br>
6.  Enhance the +Evade/+Parry styles to increase the chance more.<br>
7.  Sense Aggression<br>
