<br>
Capped quickness = 300.  (300 - 60) / 6 = 40  That is, approximately a 40% haste effect from quickness.<br>
<br>
Based on a 3.5 weapon speed:<br>
<br>
3.5dps * (100% - 40%) = 2.1dps<br>
<br>
To figure for maximum useful haste:<br>
<br>
1.5dps / 2.1dps = 0.714<br>
1 - 0.714 = 0.286<br>
<br>
So if you have capped quickness, only a 28% haste effect is useful.  But, of course, our haste goes up to 39%.  I suppose this means that we can forgo a good portion of quickness buffing, or that we'll still be in good shape after we're debuffed or our buffs fail.  But, you want quickness anyway since it also apparently effects evading, and I'm not entirely comfortable with &quot;you can buff yourself way higher than your cap so that later on you can still be okay.&quot;  Especially since we're paying for our buffs in blood.<br>
<br>
This could mean that the haste buff is actually less useful than it seems at the highest levels. <p>Harana Nyao - Guinevere - Valkyn Savage<br>
